             was indicted for <rs id="t18311201-242-off1287" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18311201-242-off1287" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18311201-242-off1287" type="offenceSubcategory" value="pocketpicking"></interp>
               stealing, on the <rs id="t18311201-242-cd1288" type="crimeDate">11th of November</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18311201-242-off1287 t18311201-242-cd1288"></join>, 1 handkerchief, value 1s. 6d. the goods of 
                     <persName id="t18311201-242-victim1855" type="victimName">
                        Thomas 
                        Hill
                     <interp inst="t18311201-242-victim1855" type="surname" value="Hill"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18311201-242-victim1855" type="given" value="Thomas"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18311201-242-victim1855" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18311201-242-off1287 t18311201-242-victim1855"></join>
                     </persName>
                  , from his person
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>THOMAS HILL. I am a <rs id="t18311201-242-viclabel1289" type="occupation">sail-maker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18311201-242-victim1855 t18311201-242-viclabel1289"></join>. On the 11th of November I was in <placeName id="t18311201-242-crimeloc1290">Ratcliff-highway</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18311201-242-crimeloc1290" type="placeName" value="Ratcliff-highway"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18311201-242-crimeloc1290" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18311201-242-off1287 t18311201-242-crimeloc1290"></join>, between six and seven o'clock at night; I felt something at my right side - I turned, and saw the prisoner; he put his face close to me, and said, "What do you want with me?" I said Nothing - he repeated it again and I said Nothing; I then felt my pocket, and missed my handkerchief; I<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183112010108"></xptr>said, "I have lost my handkerchief;" he said, "I saw two urchin thieves on the other side of the way;" he walked with me a little way, till we came to a light; I saw a bulk in front of him, and my handkerchief was hanging down - he walked on to a turning which was no thoroughfare; he turned to go down - I seized him, and cried Stop thief! he struck me - he had a black handkerchief in his hand; I took my handkerchief from under his coat.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. STURGEON. Q. Did he not ask whether you had lost a handkerchief? No - he was intoxicated, but could walk very well.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18311201-242-person1856">
                  JOHN 
                  EASTERBROOK
               <interp inst="t18311201-242-person1856" type="surname" value="EASTERBROOK"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18311201-242-person1856" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18311201-242-person1856" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am the officer. I saw the prisoner with this black handkerchief in his hand, and the prosecutor gave me this other.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence I was going to see a friend, and I saw this handkerchief on the ground - I took it up, and walked on; when I came to this street I turned, and the gentleman came up to me; I said, "What do you want?" he saw this handkerchief hang down - he caught hold of it; I took it out, and gave it to him.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18311201-242-verdict1291" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18311201-242-verdict1291" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 20. - <rs id="t18311201-242-punish1292" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18311201-242-punish1292" type="punishmentCategory" value="transport"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t18311201-242-defend1854 t18311201-242-punish1292"></join>
               Transported for Seven Years
            </rs>.</p>
